702796f-b.title: Brooklyn: 60th Street - 18th Avenue
702796f-b.text:
60th Stroot, north side, west of 18th Avenue (lot 53), showing
a framo home, owned for many years by F. Aiello. It first
appears on Robinson's map of 1898 and is a typical oxample of
tha "architoctural monstrocities" whiah were not infrequontly
built in the latter part of tho ninoteonth century.
